annotation.TEXT: Okay, I'm back here again, but this time, I won't be taking that pipe (obviously).
Oh, and I've gotta pay attention to Mr. Urchin here, too.
BARF!!!
Ooh, and there's stuff behind him!
NOOOOO!!! My shell!!! ...Oh, well.
Whoa, almost got poked in the butt there!
Hmm... Can I slide-kill that fuzzy?
Ooh, cape! I'll certainly take that!
Whoa, no you don't! I think I'll return this shell to sender.
Whoa, where'd that torpedo come from?
Gotta check every pipe...
Yep, barely. (That was a little risky.)
Oh, man. Well, that Chuck's well-protected. I don't think I'll be able to shoot him down before he wakes all the sleeping fishies. I'd better fry said fishies then.
Okay, let's see what's in these Cerulean Depths...
Oh, but of course, it's not over yet, as I've got to go for this Yoshi coin...
Bob-omb Brothers? Really? At least Mouser took multiple hits to kill, and he was only hurt by explosions. You guys are just wusses.
Line up carefully for the Yoshi coin.
BGM: Custom - Mystery Deeps by MidiGuy
Okay, thankfully, this level is over and done with, and I somehow survived it.

Last time, on Bowser Rampages again... I conquered Frozen Castle, and have unlocked a path leading to Cerulean City, where I'll have a chance to battle Misty for the Cascade Badge. Wait... that's another game.
Ha! You can't get me that way, Shell Brother!
Double kill!
Oh, good. The cheepos have stopped. Wow, how did I not get hit during all that?
I guess I can't clobber the boomerangs with a shell.
Whoa, I descended faster than I expected there. That would've sucked if I fell off the screen and died there!
Ow. Yeah, I was expecting that. I really don't like this room very much.
Oh, and there was an off screen ceiling back there that almost screwed me over.
Somebody should make a custom graphic of a saw wearing glasses, so you can call it a "see-saw".
Oof! But you can get me that way...
I guess I should keep my eyes peeled for a P-switch...
Wow, only 29? Well, at least I get a reserve feather from the shell I carried across the finish line...
Oh, man. This part looks tricky.

Oh, god. I remember this part now. These stationary spike balls are evil. They're actually objects, basically like four munchers in a 2x2 square. However, the spike balls' graphics don't look square, so be careful around them, especially near their corners, since you will get hit before it looks like you've physically touched them.
Aha. I did want to go right first, since it's a short dead-end with a power up that I'll want.
Whoa there, boomerang.
On second thought, I want to take a look at what's to the right first.
There's my P-switch. However, I believe I didn't pick up every single coin from fried RVFs earlier, so I'd better watch out for respawns.
I'll take that power up, and then down the pipe I go!
BGM: Pok√©mon Gold/Silver/Crystal - Dark Cave
...Or not. Uh, game? Where's my feather? Did it get stuck in the ceiling? Man, I hate it when that happens! It just feels unfair to be gypped like that.
Yep, there they are. Just back off a bit and then torch them again.
Uh, whoops. Maybe it's still in play?
Ha, I'm not falling for that again! Now, take this!
I so want to get revenge on that guy, but common sense is telling me to think about my safety here.
Really? All that's over here is six coins? Seems almost not worth it. (Unless maybe there's something else hidden here that I'm not aware of...)
Toasty! Finally. That only took forever and a half.
I have no idea how I did not get hit there. I remember this place being a royal pain last time I played through this hack.
And now to go left to proceed with the stage. It's not very often that you encounter a level where left is the main direction to go.
And just like that, secret exit.
Oh, man. It's a switch palace! But, I'm going to hold off on that for the moment and head back to Deep Caverns 1 for the normal exit.
I am so totally going to fry your sorry butt! (Wait, do plants have butts?)
Good. I needed a power up.

And that unlocks Deep Caverns 2. Well, which of these two levels should I head to next? I bet I know what the result will be, but I'll have you guys vote anyway, and we'll find out where I'm going next time!
Ha! I screwed up your aim, and now to screw you up!
Oh, no. No! NOOOOO!!! Not the flying cheepos! This is gonna be insane!
DIE, EVILDOER!!!
Gah!!! I will get my revenge on you!
I really want to destroy this guy.
Alright, let's explore Deep Caverns 1. It's a red level, so that means there's most likely a fork in the road here that will result in me opening up the voting booths for you guys later.
Wow, I guess we really are exploring the depths here.
Oh, man. Jelectros. Maybe holding a shell isn't a good idea here. Well, I can at least take out an Urchin with it.
Torpedo Ted launchers? Yeah, maybe I should ditch the shell before it causes a "killed" torpedo to careen into me at a crazy angle.
Oh, cool. We've got the MegaMari Cirno music playing again!
Whoa, they're trying to flank me or something here!
I know better than to rush forward when there's a Boomerang Bro. at the start of a level!
Oh, man. It's like Way Cool all over again. (Well, the part of Way Cool that often gets skipped since most people would rather take the Yoshi wings exit.)
Midpoint and a yellow ! block. Good, I can get a couple of HP back.
Oh, and I'm not gonna bother with most of the out-of-the-way coins here.
Hmm... There's a P-switch. It's probably needed to get the secret exit.
Hmm... Do I go left or right? Let's try left first.
To be continued...

Another reason I consider these spike balls evil-- Just look at this narrow passage! It's almost impossible for a big plumber to get through without getting hit, and the non-intuitive hitboxes on the spike balls don't help!
And with this Yoshi coin, my score passes the million mark!
Okay, it's still here, and it landed right next to where I need to use it.
Oh, man. How long does this level go on?
Ah, I believe I can fry Chuck from this side, not that it matters now.
Watch out for those evil hexagons!
Argh! And then I headbutt a Jelectro while trying to control my swimming movements while holding an item...
Double kill!
